quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  38,43,And We gave him his family and the like of them with them (doubled his family) as a mercy from Us and as a reminder for the people of understanding (reasonable people)
  38,44,"(We told him:) take a bunch (of hay) in your hand and strike with it and do not break your oath. Indeed We found him patient, the good servant, indeed he was repentant"
  38,45,"And remember Our servants, Abraham and Isaac and Jacob, men of power and insight"
  38,46,And We made them devoted by sincerely remembering the home (of the hereafter)
  38,47,And indeed they are among the best of the chosen in Our view
  38,48,"And remember Ishmael and Al-Yasa'a (Elisha) and Zul-kifl (man of the responsibility), all among the best"
  38,49,"This (Quran) is a reminder, and indeed for those who control themselves is a good place of return"
  38,50,"Eternal gardens, with the doors opened for them"
  38,51,"reclining (and relaxing) in them, they call for many fruits and drinks in them"
  38,52,and there are girls of equal age and restrained glances with them
  38,53,This is what you are promised for the day of accounting
  38,54,"Indeed this is Our provision, which there is no end to it"
  38,55,"This (is for the believers), and for the rebellious there is a bad place of return"
  38,56,"Hell, they enter (and burn in) it, and it is a bad resting place"
  38,57,"This (is for the disbelievers), so they should taste it, boiling water and pus"
  38,58,and other kinds of that type
  38,59,"This is a group rushing (and pushing) with you, there is no welcome to them, indeed they enter (and burn in) the fire"
  38,60,"They say: no, there is no welcome to you (either), you brought it upon us, and it is a bad place to stay"
  38,61,"They say: our Master, whoever brought this upon us, then double (or multiply) his punishment in the fire"